The paper deals with the problem of minimizing the age of information (AoI) in energy-constrained networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The paper also involves optimization and control theory, which are subfields of information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY), respectively. The use of weighted average peak age suggests that the paper may also involve some form of statistical analysis or machine learning (cs.MA). Finally, the paper proposes a simple-to-implement algorithm, which could fall under the category of machine learning or artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
